    "data privacy and genetic testing) and acting ethically and with integrity, but this concern is primarily up to the organisation to manage, particularly within their environmental, social, and governance framework.",
    "Whilst the IFoA's charter notes that \"the objects [of the IFoA] shall be, in the public interest\", what this comprises is not explicitly stated (IFoA, 2010).",
    "Additionally, this does underpin the sentiment of the Actuaries' Code (IFoA, 2019) which notes that members should act with integrity and speak up if they believe any action is unethical.",
    "In addition, regulation around bias and discrimination (see section 3.1) promotes the public interest, for example, the Equality Act (2010).",
    "Furthermore, big data is sometimes seen as a potential threat to the public interest and various data regulations try to ensure the privacy of the public."
